WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.200 --> 00:00:41.000
Before Agra was known as the holy city to the Taj Mahal. Akbar declared “with all its grandeur and glory, it became once more the abode of the caliphate, and the centre of the Sultanate.” Agra would become the new capital of the Mughal empire.
The old fort would be torn down and a stronger structure would be built in its place.


2
00:00:41.000 --> 00:01:20.000
The river Jamna holds a special relationship with the fort. An intention of Akbar himself. He he realized, like Babur before him, that water was sacred. It would become an integral aspect of his fort and would provide for his people and gardens. When Akbar travelled along the River Jamna, he recognized the spirituality, strength and good fortune of the city of Agra.

3
00:01:20.000 --> 00:02:07.000
“The excavation was made through seven strata of earth”. The old fort at Agra had been in major disrepair, therefore the workers had to work tirelessly to tear down the old fort which “the pillars had been shaken by the revolutions of time”. A new fort would be the  foundation of the strength of the empire and the new capital.

4
00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:42.000
Every single day 4,000 workers, each with specific and grueling duties, carried out the construction of the fort. The shirtless workers were strong, and we able to lift and carry stone. These labourers were not concerned with the minor details. The clothed workers were refined and worked together to perfect the details of the beautiful fort.

5
00:02:42.800 --> 00:03:10.000
The Agra fort, red hewn sandstone so joined together not a “strand of hair could find a place between them.” Many skilled men each day were brought in to actively achieve this great fortress. With these men, brought work animals and techniques. The fort was finished in eight years, from there it stood tall as the landmark of Agra.

6
00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:37.000
The Dehli gate inside the Fort at Agra. The gate known as “Elephant Gate” was opened to one of the four quarters of the world . The pillars of the gate are massive and cylindrical. Perpendicular to the pillars is a blue and yellow frieze which displays beautiful symbols.

7
00:03:37.000 --> 00:04:04.000
“lofty minded mathematicians and able  architects laid the foundation of this great building in an hour which was supreme for establishing a fortress.” The very best of the empire was brought in to ensure that the structure was properly sound and sturdy

8
00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:47.000
The Taj Mahal would then take up residence in the city of Agra, however the fort would not be in its shadow. Agra laid the foundation to the specific architectural aspects. Geometry was held with high regard as well as symmetry, hierarchy, Uniformity and symbolism.
